WEBVTT

00:06.963 --> 00:08.530
Ned: MY MOM DIED

00:08.573 --> 00:10.749
AND MY FATHER DESERTED ME
IN BOARDING SCHOOL WHEN I WAS 9.

00:10.793 --> 00:13.056
I HAVEN'T SEEN OR HEARD
FROM THE MAN IN 20 YEARS.

00:13.100 --> 00:14.710
I'M CHARLOTTE'S MOTHER.

00:14.753 --> 00:16.494
OH, MY GOD.
LILY IS CHUCK'S MOTHER.

00:16.538 --> 00:18.322
I'M HAPPY THAT I KNOW
I HAVE A MOTHER WHO'S ALIVE

00:18.366 --> 00:20.933
AND NOT SO HAPPY
SHE CAN'T KNOW I'M ALIVE.

00:20.977 --> 00:23.893
SOMEBODY ALWAYS LOVING SOMEBODY
THEY SHOULDN'T BE LOVING.

00:23.936 --> 00:25.460
I'M QUITTING YOU!

00:25.503 --> 00:27.766
THIS IS YOUR HOME.
WHERE WILL YOU GO?

00:27.810 --> 00:28.811
I KNOW A PLACE.

00:28.854 --> 00:29.812
[ OPERA SINGING ]

00:29.855 --> 00:31.596
SHUSH, SHUSH!

00:31.640 --> 00:33.381
I CAME HERE TO KEEP YOUR SECRET

00:33.424 --> 00:35.687
BUT I'M STAYING
TO KEEP ONE OF MY OWN.

00:35.731 --> 00:37.428
ONE THAT I COULD NEVER TELL YOU.

00:37.472 --> 00:38.473
TELL ME.

00:38.516 --> 00:39.517
I STILL LOVE THE PIE-MAKER.

00:39.561 --> 00:41.345
AND HE LOVES SOMEONE ELSE.

00:41.389 --> 00:43.956
YOU'RE THINKING ABOUT LIVING
HERE NOW, AREN'T YOU?

00:44.000 --> 00:46.350
I'M NOT MOVING OUT,
I'M JUST MOVING NEXT DOOR.

00:47.569 --> 00:48.657
YOU WANNA COME HOME?

00:48.700 --> 00:49.658
I DO.

00:49.701 --> 00:51.312
COME ON, PIGBY.

00:51.355 --> 00:52.530
Hmm.

00:52.574 --> 00:54.315
LET'S BE ROOMMATES.

00:54.358 --> 00:55.620
WELCOME HOME.

00:55.664 --> 00:57.274
HUMANS AND DOGS ARE THE SAME.

00:57.318 --> 01:00.321
SUPPLY THE RIGHT CUE,
AND THEY RESPOND ACCORDINGLY.

01:00.364 --> 01:02.671
- SLICK.
- YOU DON'T KNOW SLICK.

01:02.714 --> 01:03.846
Mm-hmm.

01:05.543 --> 01:08.329
Narrator: THERE ONCE WAS
A PIE-MAKER WHO HAD A GIFT

01:08.372 --> 01:10.896
A TOUCH THAT BROUGHT
THE DEAD TO LIFE.

01:10.940 --> 01:12.811
THE GIFT FOLLOWED THESE RULES.

01:12.855 --> 01:15.205
TOUCH A DEAD THING ONCE, ALIVE.

01:15.249 --> 01:18.904
TOUCH A DEAD THING TWICE,
DEAD AGAIN FOREVER.

01:18.948 --> 01:21.559
KEEP A DEAD THING ALIVE
FOR MORE THAN A MINUTE...

01:21.603 --> 01:24.214
...SOMETHING ELSE HAS TO DIE.

01:25.737 --> 01:27.696
[ THEME MUSIC ]

01:38.359 --> 01:41.013
Narrator: LONG WEEKENDS AT THE
LONGBOROUGH SCHOOL FOR BOYS

01:41.057 --> 01:42.667
WERE A QUIET TIME

01:42.711 --> 01:45.931
AS MOST CHILDREN WENT HOME
TO THEIR FAMILIES.

01:45.975 --> 01:47.672
THERE WERE
THOSE STUDENTS, HOWEVER

01:47.716 --> 01:49.718
WHO GATHERED
NOT OUT OF FRIENDSHIP

01:49.761 --> 01:52.721
BUT BECAUSE THEY HAD
NOWHERE ELSE TO GO.

01:52.764 --> 01:57.639
YOUNG NED FOUND HIMSELF A MEMBER
OF THIS ELITE GROUP.

01:57.682 --> 02:01.425
INGMAR TODD WAS THE SON
OF ROVING MISSIONARIES.

02:01.469 --> 02:03.645
AS THERE WAS
VERY LITTLE ELSE TO DO

02:03.688 --> 02:06.865
INGMAR'S ROOM BECAME
A CENTER OF ACTIVITY.

02:06.909 --> 02:08.824
[ German accent ]
PLACE YOUR BETS, GENTLEMEN.

02:08.867 --> 02:10.478
Narrator: HE HAD ARRIVED
AT BOARDING SCHOOL

02:10.521 --> 02:15.004
WITH A PROFESSIONALLY CERTIFIED
AND BALANCED ROULETTE WHEEL

02:15.047 --> 02:18.050
AND A TAWNY OWL NAMED CASPER.

02:18.094 --> 02:21.141
ALL YOUNG NED HAD TO WAGER
WAS THE BOX OF CHOCOLATES

02:21.184 --> 02:23.360
HE'D HASTILY SNUCK
INTO HIS SUITCASE

02:23.404 --> 02:27.930
THE DAY HIS FATHER DROPPED HIM
OFF AT BOARDING SCHOOL.

02:27.973 --> 02:32.500
IT WAS THEN HE NOTICED
THE NOTE TUCKED INTO THE BOX.

02:32.543 --> 02:35.155
HE REALIZED THE INDIVIDUALLY
WRAPPED CHOCOLATES

02:35.198 --> 02:39.115
CURRENTLY IN PLAY HAD BEEN
INTENDED AS A GIFT TO HIM

02:39.159 --> 02:41.030
FROM HIS DEARLY DEPARTED MOTHER.

02:41.073 --> 02:46.427
BETS ARE CLOSED.

02:46.470 --> 02:47.776
Narrator:
LIKE MANY BEGINNING PLAYERS

02:47.819 --> 02:50.822
YOUNG NED BET
ON BOTH RED AND BLACK

02:50.866 --> 02:54.174
BUT FAILED TO CONSIDER
THE DOUBLE ZERO ON THE WHEEL.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.959
DOUBLE ZED. HOUSE WINS.

02:57.002 --> 02:58.743
Narrator:
HE LOST EVERYTHING.

02:58.787 --> 03:00.528
THE LESSON WAS CLEAR --

03:00.571 --> 03:03.966
IN GAMBLING, NO MATTER HOW WELL
YOU THINK YOU KNOW THE ODDS

03:04.009 --> 03:07.143
THERE'S ALWAYS AN OUTCOME
YOU CAN'T SEE COMING.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.971
DURING THE YEARS THAT FOLLOWED

03:09.014 --> 03:11.756
THE PIE MAKER AVOIDED
TAKING GAMBLES

03:11.800 --> 03:14.194
WITH A FEW NOTABLE EXCEPTIONS.

03:14.237 --> 03:17.240
HE INVESTED HIS LIFE SAVINGS
IN A BAKERY AT A TIME

03:17.284 --> 03:20.417
WHEN CARBOHYDRATES HAD FALLEN
COMPLETELY OUT OF FASHION

03:20.461 --> 03:22.593
AND MORE IMPORTANTLY

03:22.637 --> 03:25.988
HE HAD GAMBLED ON THE LOVE
OF HIS CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART

03:26.031 --> 03:29.905
THE GIRL NEXT DOOR
WHO HAD RETURNED FROM THE DEAD.

03:29.948 --> 03:31.254
MMM. TRY THIS.

03:31.298 --> 03:32.255
LIKE THE FORK.

03:32.299 --> 03:34.518
LIKE BEING ALIVE.

03:34.562 --> 03:36.303
IT'S A NEW FLAVOR --
SPRING PASSION FRUIT.

03:36.346 --> 03:37.826
NOW, I KNOW
IT'S NOT SPRING HERE

03:37.869 --> 03:39.436
BUT IT IS IN NEW ZEALAND

03:39.480 --> 03:40.916
WHICH IS, UH, EXOTIC
AND UPSIDE DOWN

03:40.959 --> 03:42.700
WHICH IS HOW
WE COULD SERVE IT.

03:42.744 --> 03:45.616
Narrator: BETTING ON CHUCK
HAD MADE THE PIE MAKER HAPPIER

03:45.660 --> 03:47.401
THAN HE HAD EVER BEEN.

03:47.444 --> 03:48.619
WE'LL PUT IT ON THE MENU.

03:48.663 --> 03:50.099
OOH! I LIKE DARING NED.

03:50.142 --> 03:51.405
IT SEEMS SINCE YOU ARRIVED

03:51.448 --> 03:53.233
CAUTIOUS NED
HAS LEFT THE BUILDING.

03:53.276 --> 03:55.452
UH, WHO'S THE NEW GUY
IN THE BOOTH?

03:55.496 --> 03:58.412
THE HANDSOME, BROODING OLDER MAN
WITH A SENSUAL TWINKLE?

03:58.455 --> 04:01.545
PLUS, HE SMELLS GOOD.

04:01.589 --> 04:03.591
HE MUMBLED SOMETHING ODD
TO ME EARLIER.

04:03.634 --> 04:06.985
Narrator:
THERE WAS NO WORD THAT
COMPLETELY DESCRIBED THE FEELING

04:07.029 --> 04:10.293
THE SQUARE-SHOULDERED OLDER MAN
HAD GIVEN THE PIE MAKER.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.339
DO YOU EVER SHIVER
WHEN YOU PEE?

04:12.382 --> 04:14.166
THAT'S HOW I FELT
WHEN HE SPOKE.

04:14.210 --> 04:15.472
MORE COFFEE?

04:15.516 --> 04:18.649
MM. THANKS.
PIE IS DELICIOUS.

04:18.693 --> 04:21.478
AS GOOD AS YOUR MOTHER'S.

04:21.522 --> 04:23.088
[ GRUNTS LIGHTLY ]

04:23.132 --> 04:24.612
HE SAID THAT?

04:24.655 --> 04:26.918
- WELL, DID HE KNOW YOUR MOTHER?
- I DIDN'T ASK.

04:26.962 --> 04:28.746
A STRANGER SAYS A STRANGE
THING IN PASSING

04:28.790 --> 04:30.792
CHANCES ARE I MISHEARD HIM
OR MISUNDERSTOOD.

04:30.835 --> 04:33.098
MAYBE WHEN HE SAID
"YOUR MOTHER'S PIE"

04:33.142 --> 04:34.578
HE DIDN'T MEAN MY MOTHER

04:34.622 --> 04:36.101
HE MEANT
EVERYONE'S MOTHER --

04:36.145 --> 04:37.668
THE ICONIC
ALL-AMERICAN MOTHER

04:37.712 --> 04:39.409
CREATED BY ADVERTISERS
AND POLITICIANS

04:39.453 --> 04:41.629
AS A SHORTHAND
FOR FAMILY VALUES

04:41.672 --> 04:43.761
AND A LONGING
FOR BAKED GOODS.

04:43.805 --> 04:45.502
WOULD THAT
MAKE YOU SHIVER?

04:45.546 --> 04:47.156
IF SOMEONE SAID SOMETHING
TO ME ABOUT MY FAMILY

04:47.199 --> 04:48.723
IT WOULD GIVE ME
THE PISS-JITTERS

04:48.766 --> 04:50.507
BUT I'D ASK HIM ABOUT IT,
NOT HIDE IN A KITCHEN.

04:50.551 --> 04:53.554
I'M NOT HIDING.

04:53.597 --> 04:55.773
I THINK HE'S CUTE.

04:59.342 --> 05:02.084
Hi.

05:02.127 --> 05:04.347
I'M...PROBABLY MAKING
A MOUNTAIN OUT OF A MOLEHILL

05:04.391 --> 05:06.436
OVER A RANDOM COMMENT
I PROBABLY MISHEARD

05:06.480 --> 05:08.090
AND I'M HOPING TO OFFSET
ANY AWKWARDNESS

05:08.133 --> 05:09.744
YOU ARE
OR WILL BE FEELING

05:09.787 --> 05:12.877
BY PROVIDING YOUR SLICE
OF THREE-PLUM ON THE HOUSE.

05:12.921 --> 05:16.141
YOU'RE A NERVOUS TALKER...
LIKE YOUR DAD.

05:16.185 --> 05:18.927
THIS COMPLICATES THINGS.
YOU MAY NEED TO PAY FOR THE PIE.

05:18.970 --> 05:20.972
[ CHUCKLES ]
LOOK. DWIGHT DIXON.

05:21.016 --> 05:23.366
I WAS A FRIEND OF YOUR FATHER'S
25 YEARS AGO.

05:23.410 --> 05:25.542
I MEAN, YOU ARE NED,
AM I RIGHT?

05:25.586 --> 05:26.891
NOPE.

05:26.935 --> 05:30.112
YES, YOU ARE, SILLY.
HI. I'M OLIVE.

05:30.155 --> 05:31.505
HI, OLIVE.
Chuck: I'M KITTY.

05:31.548 --> 05:33.376
KITTY PIMMS.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

05:33.420 --> 05:35.509
UH, SO YOU KNEW
NED'S PARENTS?

05:35.552 --> 05:38.033
YEAH, BACK, UH,
WHEN THEY WERE DATING.

05:38.076 --> 05:40.078
IT WAS THE PEAK
OF PEACH SEASON.

05:40.122 --> 05:42.080
SHE BAKED
A BROWN-SUGAR CRUST.

05:42.124 --> 05:43.386
[ Chuckling ]
YOUR DAD DIDN'T HAVE A CHANCE.

05:43.430 --> 05:44.692
THEY NEVER MENTIONED YOU.

05:44.735 --> 05:46.433
OH, I WAS IN THE SERVICE
WITH YOUR DAD

05:46.476 --> 05:48.086
BACK BEFORE YOU WERE BORN.

05:48.130 --> 05:50.045
YOU KNOW WHAT? YOUR DAD
DIDN'T LIKE TO REMINISCE.

05:50.088 --> 05:51.699
PROBABLY A LOT OF THINGS
HE DIDN'T TALK ABOUT.

05:51.742 --> 05:53.091
SOUNDS FAMILIAR.

05:53.135 --> 05:54.702
I'M ACTUALLY
TRYING TO FIND HIM.

05:54.745 --> 05:56.747
I WAS HOPING
YOU COULD HELP.

05:56.791 --> 05:58.706
REALLY LOVE TO SEE HIM.

05:58.749 --> 06:00.490
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:00.534 --> 06:02.666
YOU GOT HIS FACE, YOU KNOW,
ESPECIALLY AROUND THE EYES.

06:02.710 --> 06:05.930
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER HAD HOPED NEVER
TO BE LIKENED TO HIS FATHER

06:05.974 --> 06:07.367
WHETHER IT BE
AROUND THE EYES...

06:07.410 --> 06:08.498
I'M AFRAID
WE LOST TOUCH...

06:08.542 --> 06:09.586
...OR THE HEART.

06:09.630 --> 06:10.718
...20 YEARS AGO.

06:10.761 --> 06:12.546
OH, THAT'S A SHAME.

06:12.589 --> 06:14.374
ANY THOUGHTS
ON WHERE I MIGHT LOOK?

06:14.417 --> 06:16.158
NOPE. AND THOUGH
YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY SPEAKING

06:16.201 --> 06:18.943
FROM A GOOD AND HELPFUL PLACE,
IT'S NOT GOOD AND HELPFUL...

06:18.987 --> 06:20.684
TO ME, SO...

06:20.728 --> 06:23.426
Narrator: AS CHUCK MARVELED
AT THE PIE MAKER'S REFUSAL

06:23.470 --> 06:25.950
TO HELP SEARCH
FOR HIS ONLY PARENT

06:25.994 --> 06:29.258
EMERSON COD MARVELED
AT THE DIGESTIVE COMA

06:29.301 --> 06:32.217
PRODUCED BY BEEF BALLS
AND CURRIED CUTTLEFISH

06:32.261 --> 06:34.611
FROM THE DIM SUM RESTAURANT
DOWNSTAIRS.

06:35.612 --> 06:37.135
HIS PHONE SILENCED

06:37.179 --> 06:39.964
EMERSON KNEW THE WORLD
OF CLIENTS AND MURDERS

06:40.008 --> 06:45.535
WOULD SOON BE LOST IN THE CLOUD
OF A POWER NAP.

06:45.579 --> 06:47.407
WHAT THE HELL?

06:56.198 --> 06:59.201
Narrator: ARRIVING DOWNSTAIRS
IN SEARCH OF A NEW CASE

06:59.244 --> 07:02.030
THE P.I. STUMBLED ON ONE
FROM HIS PAST...

07:02.073 --> 07:03.205
[ CLICKER CLICKS ]

07:03.248 --> 07:04.685
...SIMONE HUNDIN

07:04.728 --> 07:06.730
OBEDIENCE EXPERT AND WIDOW

07:06.774 --> 07:10.386
OF DECEASED POLYGAMOUS
DOG BREEDER, HAROLD HUNDIN.

07:10.430 --> 07:12.562
WHILE INVESTIGATING
HER HUSBAND'S MURDER

07:12.606 --> 07:16.087
EMERSON AND SIMONE
HAD FORGED A CLOSE BOND.

07:16.131 --> 07:17.524
EMERSON COD.

07:17.567 --> 07:20.701
SIMONE.
WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN UP TO?

07:20.744 --> 07:23.138
Narrator: IT WAS A FRIENDSHIP
THAT HAD VERY NEARLY

07:23.181 --> 07:25.445
BUT NOT QUITE, BECOME...

07:25.488 --> 07:27.142
BREEDING.

07:27.185 --> 07:29.057
MY BUBBLEGUM'S IN HEAT.
IT WAS A LONG NIGHT.

07:29.100 --> 07:30.362
[ CLICK ]
SIT.

07:30.406 --> 07:32.495
BUT WHAT A TREAT
BUMPING INTO YOU.

07:32.539 --> 07:34.715
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE
A DIM SUM CONNOISSEUR.

07:34.758 --> 07:37.021
BEST PORK BUNS IN TOWN.
MY OFFICE IS UPSTAIRS.

07:37.065 --> 07:38.414
IT'S A DANGEROUS
COMBINATION.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.763
BUN?

07:39.807 --> 07:41.548
NO, I'M REALLY TRYING TO,
YOU KNOW --

07:41.591 --> 07:44.072
[ CLICK ]
Narrator: THE PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR CONSIDERED

07:44.115 --> 07:46.248
HOW HIS INESCAPABLE DESIRE

07:46.291 --> 07:49.556
TO BE OBEDIENT
TO THIS OBEDIENCE TRAINER

07:49.599 --> 07:52.820
WAS AT ONCE THRILLING
AND TERRIFYING.

07:52.863 --> 07:54.299
THEN HE REMEMBERED HIS CASE.

07:54.343 --> 07:56.171
HEY, DID YOU SEND ME A MESSAGE
IN A COOKIE?

07:56.214 --> 07:57.912
WASN'T ME.

07:57.955 --> 08:00.523
I FIND THERE ARE MORE RELIABLE
WAYS TO SEND A MESSAGE.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.438
[ LAUGHS ]

08:03.700 --> 08:05.789
[ CLICK ]
LEAVE IT.

08:05.833 --> 08:07.835
IT'S BEEN A PLEASURE,
MR. COD.

08:07.878 --> 08:09.445
PERHAPS WE'LL CROSS
PATHS AGAIN.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.099
MM.

08:11.142 --> 08:12.753
[ CHUCKLING ]

08:14.189 --> 08:15.886
[ CLICK ]

08:17.409 --> 08:18.976
[ GRUNTS ]

08:19.020 --> 08:21.370
Narrator: FORTUNATELY,
EMERSON HAD A DISTRACTION

08:21.413 --> 08:23.851
FROM HIS CONFLICTING IMPULSES --

08:23.894 --> 08:25.809
A CLIENT.

08:28.464 --> 08:29.509
[ CRYING ]

08:29.552 --> 08:31.380
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM?

08:31.423 --> 08:34.035
I'M EMERSON COD, THE PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR FROM UPSTAIRS.

08:34.078 --> 08:35.732
DID YOU BY ANY CHANCE
CONTACT ME?

08:35.776 --> 08:39.257
I'VE SEEN
YOUR BILLBOARDS.

08:39.301 --> 08:41.259
MY NAME IS LAI DI.

08:41.303 --> 08:42.522
"LADY"?

08:42.565 --> 08:44.611
"LAI DI."

08:44.654 --> 08:47.875
I'M MARRIED TO BAO,
THE CHEF.

08:47.918 --> 08:50.051
PICKING UP SOME THINGS
OF HIS.

08:50.094 --> 08:51.574
YOU'RE MARRIED
TO THE CHEF?

08:51.618 --> 08:53.271
MA'AM, MAY I JUST SAY --

08:53.315 --> 08:55.665
YOUR HUSBAND'S PORK BUNS
MAKE ME GLAD TO BE ALIVE.

08:55.709 --> 08:57.406
THE MAN'S A TRUE ARTIST.

08:57.449 --> 08:59.930
WELL, NOT ANYMORE.

08:59.974 --> 09:01.453
HE'S DEAD NOW.

09:01.497 --> 09:05.501
BUT I'LL HIRE YOU TO FIND
WHO KILLED HIM.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.416
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

09:07.459 --> 09:10.811
LAI DI AND HER HUSBAND, BAO,
IMMIGRATED FROM BEIJING

09:10.854 --> 09:14.771
WITH THE HOPE OF OPENING
THEIR OWN RESTAURANT.

09:14.815 --> 09:17.034
BAO QUICKLY ESTABLISHED HIMSELF

09:17.078 --> 09:18.775
AS THE PREMIER AUTHORITY

09:18.819 --> 09:22.518
ON THE DELICATE ART
OF BUN STEAMING.

09:22.562 --> 09:25.260
HE DEMANDED PRIVACY
WHILE HE WORKED...

09:25.303 --> 09:27.349
BOTH TO ELIMINATE DISTRACTIONS

09:27.392 --> 09:30.221
AND PROTECT HIS UNIQUE RECIPES.

09:30.265 --> 09:32.876
BUT EVEN WITH HIS DAUGHTER
WORKING AS A WAITRESS

09:32.920 --> 09:35.052
BAO COULD NEVER SAVE
ENOUGH MONEY

09:35.096 --> 09:36.706
FOR HIS OWN RESTAURANT.

09:36.750 --> 09:38.621
IT WAS AFTER A 16-HOUR SHIFT

09:38.665 --> 09:41.581
THAT LAI DI HAD NOTICED
BAO COULD NOT SLEEP.

09:41.624 --> 09:44.018
SOMETHING HAD HIM TERRIFIED.

09:44.061 --> 09:46.586
BAO CHOSE TO REPLY
IN ENGLISH.

09:46.629 --> 09:49.458
- PRESSURE!
- PRESSURE?

09:49.501 --> 09:56.073
Narrator: LAI DI WOULD REMEMBER
BAO'S MISGIVING AS IRONIC.

09:56.117 --> 09:59.468
POLICE WERE SATISFIED BAO'S
DEATH HAD BEEN AN ACCIDENT

09:59.511 --> 10:02.950
BUT LAI DI WAS CONVINCED
THERE HAD BEEN FOUL PLAY.

10:02.993 --> 10:05.953
OKAY, LET'S BE DELICATE.
HE MAY NOT SPEAK ENGLISH.

10:05.996 --> 10:07.302
AND WITH THE PIPE
THE WAY IT IS,

10:07.345 --> 10:10.174
I DON'T KNOW
IF HE'LL SPEAK AT ALL.

10:14.352 --> 10:15.484
YOU SPEAK CHINESE?

10:15.527 --> 10:18.400
AAH!
AAAAAH!

10:18.443 --> 10:20.271
[ SCREAMS ]
WHOA! WATCH OUT.

10:20.315 --> 10:22.578
PLEASE, DON'T HURT ME!
I'M SORRY I LOSE THE BET!

10:22.622 --> 10:24.188
LOOK, WE'RE NOT
GONNA HURT YOU!

10:24.232 --> 10:26.364
WHAT BET?
GAMBLING AT THE DIM SUM!

10:26.408 --> 10:27.888
NOW SOMEONE'S
GOING TO KILL ME.

10:27.931 --> 10:29.280
GOING TO KILL YOU?

10:29.324 --> 10:30.847
I DON'T KNOW HOW
THEY'RE GOING TO DO IT

10:30.891 --> 10:32.327
BUT THEY'RE GOING
TO DO IT FOR SURE!

10:32.370 --> 10:33.937
YEAH, YEAH,
WHO -- WHO WANTS TO KILL YOU?

10:33.981 --> 10:35.547
WHO WERE YOU
GAMBLING WITH?

10:35.591 --> 10:37.767
I TELL YOU THAT,
AND I'M A DEAD MAN!

10:37.811 --> 10:39.551
SEE, WHAT WE NEED NOW
IS A MIRROR.

10:39.595 --> 10:41.858
- I GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE!
- HEY!

10:41.902 --> 10:43.077
BAO, NO! WAIT!

10:43.120 --> 10:44.818
[ CLANG, BAO GRUNTS ]

10:44.861 --> 10:46.036
OUCH.

10:55.480 --> 10:58.614
Narrator: AS IT APPEARED THE BUN
STEAMER'S BUNS WERE STEAMED

10:58.658 --> 11:00.529
OVER A BET AT THE DIM SUM

11:00.572 --> 11:02.618
EMERSON COD RETURNED
TO THE RESTAURANT

11:02.662 --> 11:05.273
FOR A CHAT WITH BAO'S DAUGHTER.

11:05.316 --> 11:06.883
Mei: I DON'T KNOW WHY
MY MOTHER HIRED YOU.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.885
MY FATHER'S DEATH
WAS AN ACCIDENT.

11:08.929 --> 11:11.018
YOUR MOTHER HAD A HUNCH.

11:11.061 --> 11:12.628
I COULD GOLD-LEAF
MY BATHROOM

11:12.672 --> 11:14.543
WITH WHAT I MADE
OFF MOTHER-HUNCHES.

11:14.586 --> 11:16.501
AND WHAT I REALLY NEED
TO KNOW IS --

11:16.545 --> 11:20.375
ARE THOSE THE NEW
CHIU-CHAO DUMPLINGS? MAY I?

11:20.418 --> 11:22.725
PORK...

11:22.769 --> 11:23.900
...DRIED SHRIMP.

11:23.944 --> 11:25.902
CHIVES, MUSHROOMS...

11:25.946 --> 11:27.730
IN A GLUTINOUS RICE FLOUR.

11:27.774 --> 11:30.385
GIRL, YOUR FATHER COULD MAKE
A GROWN MAN CRY.

11:30.428 --> 11:31.821
HI.

11:31.865 --> 11:34.519
THIS IS RUBBIE WU,
MY FIANCE.

11:34.563 --> 11:36.565
ALSO MANAGER
OF THE DIM SUM.

11:36.608 --> 11:38.698
SON, YOU GOT A HELL
OF A RESTAURANT.

11:38.741 --> 11:41.309
AH. I'M A LUCKY MAN
IN MANY WAYS.

11:41.352 --> 11:42.919
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:42.963 --> 11:45.269
MR. COD, RIGHT?
YOU WORK UPSTAIRS.

11:45.313 --> 11:47.315
CUTTLEFISH, BEEF BALLS

11:47.358 --> 11:49.665
AND TARO DUMPLINGS
EVERY SUNDAY AT NOON.

11:49.709 --> 11:50.710
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:50.753 --> 11:52.886
I'M SORRY ABOUT YOUR LOSS

11:52.929 --> 11:56.019
BOTH IN THE HUMAN
AND GASTRONOMICAL SENSE.

11:56.063 --> 11:58.021
SPEAKING OF THE GENIUS
WHO WAS YOUR FATHER

11:58.065 --> 11:59.980
IS IT POSSIBLE HE WAS
ALSO A DEGENERATE GAMBLER?

12:00.023 --> 12:01.677
I HEARD HE WAS KILLED
OVER A BET.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.418
HE DIDN'T HAVE TIME
FOR ANYTHING BUT WORK.

12:03.461 --> 12:06.290
LEAST, AS FAR AS I KNOW.

12:06.334 --> 12:08.292
MY FATHER AND I
WEREN'T VERY CLOSE.

12:08.336 --> 12:09.816
WHAT ABOUT GAMBLING
HERE IN THE RESTAURANT

12:09.859 --> 12:12.557
YOU KNOW, WITH EMPLOYEES
OR MAYBE CUSTOMERS?

12:12.601 --> 12:14.037
WE'RE JUST
A DIM SUM RESTAURANT.

12:14.081 --> 12:16.387
IF BAO WAS IN TROUBLE
'CAUSE OF GAMBLING

12:16.431 --> 12:18.259
IT DIDN'T HAPPEN HERE.

12:18.302 --> 12:19.869
OH.

12:27.181 --> 12:29.879
SO, IT SOUNDS LIKE MEI
DIDN'T SEEM TOO BROKEN UP

12:29.923 --> 12:31.663
ABOUT DEAR OLD DEAD DAD.

12:31.707 --> 12:33.361
DIDN'T WASTE MANY TEARS.

12:33.404 --> 12:35.406
THAT BEING SAID, I SEARCHED
THE ENTIRE RESTAURANT --

12:35.450 --> 12:38.366
THERE'S NO BASEMENT OR SECRET
CARD ROOM OR THE LIKE.

12:38.409 --> 12:40.455
MAYBE BAO MEANT SOMETHING ELSE
WHEN HE SAID HE LOST A BET.

12:40.498 --> 12:41.891
MAYBE BAO HAD A PIPE
THROUGH HIS HEAD

12:41.935 --> 12:43.458
AND WE'RE CHASING SMOKE.

12:43.501 --> 12:47.854
I'LL CALL YOU
WHEN I FIND A LEAD.

12:47.897 --> 12:48.985
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

12:49.029 --> 12:53.163
I JUST --
[ MUTTERING ]

12:53.207 --> 12:54.730
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
DWIGHT STOPPED BY AGAIN.

12:54.774 --> 12:56.036
DIDN'T SAY MUCH.

12:56.079 --> 12:57.907
JUST THAT KIND,
WARM HEARTED SMILE

12:57.951 --> 12:59.691
WITH THE CRINKLY EYES THAT SAY

12:59.735 --> 13:01.824
"OH, I WISH I COULD FIND
MY OLD FRIEND, NED'S DAD

13:01.868 --> 13:03.565
BEFORE I DIE ALONE."

13:03.608 --> 13:05.654
HMM.

13:08.352 --> 13:09.658
I KNOW THAT FACE.

13:09.701 --> 13:11.312
IT'S THE
"I'M STILL WAITING TO HEAR

13:11.355 --> 13:13.357
WHY YOU WON'T HELP
YOUR FATHER'S FRIEND" FACE.

13:13.401 --> 13:16.143
NO, IT'S A "YOU DON'T
KNOW MY FACE AS WELL
AS YOU THINK" FACE.

13:16.186 --> 13:18.145
I KEEP MY FEELINGS
ABOUT MY FATHER BEHIND A DOOR

13:18.188 --> 13:20.190
THAT'S CLOSED FOR SO LONG
IT'S WALLPAPERED OVER

13:20.234 --> 13:21.975
AND YOU CAN'T SEE THE SEAMS.

13:22.018 --> 13:23.541
AND THAT'S HOW I LIKE IT.

13:23.585 --> 13:26.196
DWIGHT SHOWING UP IS LIKE
A CORNER PEELING.

13:26.240 --> 13:28.982
AND I SEE THAT PEELING CORNER,
AND I WANT TO RIP IT OFF.

13:29.025 --> 13:30.853
YOU WOULDN'T IF YOU KNEW
WHAT WAS UNDERNEATH.

13:30.897 --> 13:32.855
IN MY CASE,
IT'S A COLORFUL MIX

13:32.899 --> 13:35.945
OF ANGER, CHRONIC DISTRUST,
AND MISPLACED GUILT.

13:35.989 --> 13:38.730
MY MOM'S BEEN LYING TO ME FOR
THREE DECADES ABOUT WHO SHE IS.

13:38.774 --> 13:40.297
WE HAVE A WHOLE PILE
OF STINK TO WORK OUT

13:40.341 --> 13:41.821
AND I WOULD IF I COULD,
BUT I CAN'T.

13:41.864 --> 13:48.262
BUT YOU CAN IF YOU COULD,
AND YOU SHOULD.

13:48.305 --> 13:49.567
WHAT IS THAT?

13:49.611 --> 13:51.308
IT'S MY CLUE PAD
FOR WRITING DOWN CLUES.

13:51.352 --> 13:52.570
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:52.614 --> 13:54.007
I LOVE THAT YOU HAVE
A CLUE PAD.

13:54.050 --> 13:55.008
[ TEARS SHEET ]

13:55.051 --> 13:56.313
MY FATHER'S ADDRESS --

13:56.357 --> 13:57.924
YOU CAN GIVE IT
TO DWIGHT.

13:57.967 --> 13:59.534
THAT'S AS MUCH
AS I CAN DO.

13:59.577 --> 14:00.752
H-HOW LONG HAVE YOU
HAD THIS?

14:00.796 --> 14:02.276
A WHILE.

14:02.319 --> 14:03.799
Narrator: BY "A WHILE"

14:03.843 --> 14:06.323
THE PIE MAKER MEANT
20 YEARS, 11 MONTHS

14:06.367 --> 14:09.109
3 WEEKS, 5 DAYS, AND 6 HOURS

14:09.152 --> 14:12.112
SINCE HE HAD GOTTEN WORD,
WHILST AWAY AT BOARDING SCHOOL

14:12.155 --> 14:16.159
THAT HIS FATHER HAD MOVED ON
AND STARTED A NEW FAMILY...

14:16.203 --> 14:18.683
WITHOUT HIM.

14:22.470 --> 14:23.558
CAN I HELP YOU?

14:34.699 --> 14:36.136
OH.

14:36.179 --> 14:37.572
THIS IS HUA JIANG.

14:37.615 --> 14:39.574
HE OVERHEARD EMERSON
AT THE RESTAURANT.

14:39.617 --> 14:42.359
[ SPEAKING MANDARIN ]

14:42.403 --> 14:45.319
YEAH, HE SAID THAT
THERE'S BEEN ILLEGAL
GAMBLING AT THE DIM SUM

14:45.362 --> 14:47.234
SINCE IT OPENED
IN THE DAYS OF PROHIBITION.

14:47.277 --> 14:48.888
[ SPEAKING MANDARIN ]

14:51.020 --> 14:52.369
HE SAYS
THEY'D PULL THE SHADES

14:52.413 --> 14:54.545
AND PLAY CARDS FOR MONEY
ALL NIGHT LONG.

14:54.589 --> 14:55.851
AND WHEN YOUR LUCK
WAS RUNNING

14:55.895 --> 14:57.635
YOU'D HAVE
A WOMAN ON EACH ARM

14:57.679 --> 14:59.376
AND ALL THE MILK
YOU COULD DRINK.

14:59.420 --> 15:00.900
"MILK"?

15:00.943 --> 15:02.075
HMM, MIGHT NOT BE
THE RIGHT WORD.

15:02.118 --> 15:03.728
MY MANDARIN'S
A LITTLE RUSTY.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.774
THIS WENT ON UNTIL THE POLICE
FINALLY CAUGHT ON

15:05.817 --> 15:06.949
AND SHUT THEM DOWN.

15:06.993 --> 15:08.603
BUT HE SAYS
THEY ALWAYS FOUND A WAY

15:08.646 --> 15:10.779
TO KEEP
THE CARD GAME GOING.

15:14.522 --> 15:16.785
I'VE ALREADY SEARCHED
THE WHOLE DAMN RESTAURANT.

15:16.828 --> 15:18.439
WELL, THERE WERE GIN JOINTS
IN THE '20s

15:18.482 --> 15:19.962
THAT USED TO HAVE
UNDERGROUND PASSAGES

15:20.006 --> 15:21.485
AND SECRET PANELS

15:21.529 --> 15:23.139
AND YOU USED TO HAVE TO KNOW
THE PASSWORD --

15:23.183 --> 15:25.881
LIKE "ANTWERP"
OR "FIDDLESTICKS."

15:25.925 --> 15:27.883
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT?

15:27.927 --> 15:31.931
I WAS EXPECTING EMERSON
TO SAY SOMETHING SNARKY.

15:31.974 --> 15:33.541
EMERSON?

15:39.199 --> 15:40.896
Are we spying?
I love spying.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.289
Shut it.

15:42.332 --> 15:44.508
Hey. Isn't that...
Simone?

15:44.552 --> 15:46.815
That dog lady you dated?
Is that why we're hiding?

15:46.858 --> 15:48.382
We ain't hiding,
and we didn't date.

15:48.425 --> 15:50.036
- You wanted to.
- Yeah, and then I didn't.

15:50.079 --> 15:52.734
- Why you didn't?
- No kidding. She's gorgeous.

15:52.777 --> 15:54.779
There are complicated issues
in this situation

15:54.823 --> 15:56.303
that you need to know
nothing about

15:56.346 --> 15:58.044
except that their complexities
are so complex

15:58.087 --> 16:00.176
it makes this shallow
conversation absurd.

16:00.220 --> 16:01.569
Strange.

16:01.612 --> 16:03.136
You calling my romantic
life strange?

16:03.179 --> 16:04.833
No.

16:04.876 --> 16:07.140
It's strange none of the people
at that table are eating.

16:07.183 --> 16:10.882
Narrator:
AS THEY CONTINUED TO OBSERVE
THE DINERS WHO WERE NOT DINING

16:10.926 --> 16:13.798
SEVERAL UNUSUAL DETAILS
BECAME APPARENT --

16:13.842 --> 16:17.106
ALL PLATES AT THE TABLE
WERE COVERED WITH A LID.

16:17.150 --> 16:18.760
BEFORE SERVING

16:18.803 --> 16:25.593
THE WAITRESS WOULD SPIN
THE FOOD ON A LAZY SUSAN.

16:25.636 --> 16:28.509
EACH DINER TOOK FIVE PLATES...

16:28.552 --> 16:32.992
THEN PLACED A NUMBER OF SOYBEANS
IN THE CENTER OF THE TABLE.

16:33.035 --> 16:34.863
LET'S SEE 'EM.

16:34.906 --> 16:37.648
Narrator: WHILE THIS BEHAVIOR
DID NOT SEEM CONSISTENT

16:37.692 --> 16:39.999
WITH DINERS ENJOYING
A DIM SUM DINNER

16:40.042 --> 16:43.350
WHEN THE SCENE WAS REIMAGINED
IN A DIFFERENT WAY

16:43.393 --> 16:48.442
IT BEGAN TO MAKE SENSE.

16:48.485 --> 16:50.792
I DO LOVE WINNING.

16:50.835 --> 16:53.621
Those folks are playing
poker with food.

17:00.062 --> 17:03.805
Narrator: FACED WITH A TABLE
FULL OF UNSAVORY POKER PLAYERS

17:03.848 --> 17:06.199
EMERSON COD SUMMONED
A STEELY BRAVERY

17:06.242 --> 17:08.418
ACQUIRED FROM YEARS
OF P.I. WORK

17:08.462 --> 17:10.768
AS HE QUESTIONED WHAT WAS,
FOR HIM

17:10.812 --> 17:13.597
THE GROUP'S MOST
INTIMIDATING PLAYER --

17:13.641 --> 17:15.208
SIMONE.

17:15.251 --> 17:16.644
GIVEN THE AMOUNT OF CASH
YOU LEFT WITH

17:16.687 --> 17:17.949
IN YOUR DOGGIE BAG
LAST NIGHT

17:17.993 --> 17:19.255
I'D SAY THIS WASN'T
THE FIRST TIME

17:19.299 --> 17:21.083
YOU BEEN GAMBLING
AT THE DIM SUM.

17:21.127 --> 17:23.216
AGGRESSION IS A SIGN OF FEAR,
MR. COD.

17:23.259 --> 17:25.218
SOMETIMES AGGRESSION IS JUST
A SIGN OF BEING AGGRESSIVE

17:25.261 --> 17:27.829
WHICH I WILL BE UNTIL I CATCH
WHOEVER KILLED BAO TING.

17:27.872 --> 17:30.745
NOW TELL ME
ABOUT DIM SUM-STYLE POKER.

17:30.788 --> 17:32.094
IT'S QUITE SIMPLE.

17:32.138 --> 17:33.748
YOU GIVE THE PASSWORD
TO THE HOSTESS

17:33.791 --> 17:36.142
WHICH IS "HAO SHOU YUN,"
AND MEANS "FORTUNE" IN MANDARIN.

17:36.185 --> 17:37.926
YOU BUY IN AT THE TABLE.

17:37.969 --> 17:39.928
EACH PLATE IS A CARD AND THE
MEATS ARE THE FOUR SUITS --

17:39.971 --> 17:41.364
SHRIMP, PORK,
CHICKEN, BEEF.

17:41.408 --> 17:43.236
THE APPETIZERS REPRESENT
DIFFERENT NUMBERS.

17:43.279 --> 17:45.455
OTHER THAN THAT, IT'S
TRADITIONAL FIVE-CARD DRAW.

17:45.499 --> 17:47.370
EXCEPT YOU CAN EAT
YOUR CARDS.

17:47.414 --> 17:50.634
WHICH IS WHAT YOU DO
WHEN THE POLICE ARRIVE.

17:50.678 --> 17:52.854
DID YOU KNOW BAO TING?

17:52.897 --> 17:56.423
HIS STEAMED BUNS BLURRED
THE LINE BETWEEN EATING AND SEX

17:56.466 --> 17:58.599
BUT WE WERE NOT
ACQUAINTED.

17:58.642 --> 18:00.383
ANY OF THESE REGULARS
SEEM LIKE THE TYPE

18:00.427 --> 18:01.515
TO PUSH A PIPE
THROUGH YOUR SKULL

18:01.558 --> 18:03.952
IF YOU OWED 'EM MONEY?

18:03.995 --> 18:06.215
SHRIMPBOY'S A GANGSTER
IN CHARGE OF RUNNING THE TABLE

18:06.259 --> 18:07.695
AND PAYING OFF THE MANAGER.

18:07.738 --> 18:09.914
ANSON CHEN DID EIGHT YEARS
IN THE STATE PEN

18:09.958 --> 18:11.177
FOR ARMED ROBBERY.

18:11.220 --> 18:12.613
JIN QUIN
IS A THUG FOR HIRE.

18:12.656 --> 18:14.354
WILL DO ANYTHING
FOR A FEW DOLLARS.

18:14.397 --> 18:16.182
LOUIE LU STRANGLED
HIS MOTHER-IN-LAW

18:16.225 --> 18:18.140
GOT OFF
ON A TECHNICALITY.

18:18.184 --> 18:20.882
JIM...IS A PLUMBER.

18:20.925 --> 18:22.144
THEY ALL TAKE
GAMBLING SERIOUSLY

18:22.188 --> 18:23.711
AND THEY'RE
ALL DANGEROUS.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.365
ANY OF THEM
COULD HAVE DONE IT.

18:25.408 --> 18:28.281
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

18:28.324 --> 18:29.847
PBHT. PLEASE.

18:29.891 --> 18:31.588
I WAS AT A DOG SHOW
THAT NIGHT

18:31.632 --> 18:34.591
WHICH IS 800 ALIBIS -- 1,200,
IF YOU INCLUDE CANINES.

18:34.635 --> 18:36.724
ARE WE FINIS?

18:36.767 --> 18:38.639
[ GRUNTS ]

18:43.252 --> 18:44.993
I'VE MADE A CAREER
OUT OF TRAINING ANIMALS

18:45.036 --> 18:47.300
TO OVERCOME AND
SUBDUE THEIR INSTINCTS.

18:47.343 --> 18:49.345
THAT BEING SAID
WITHOUT RAW INSTINCT

18:49.389 --> 18:52.392
LIFE IS NOTHING MORE
THAN A SERIES OF EMPTY TRICKS.

18:52.435 --> 18:56.787
YOU PRETENDING THIS IS
ALL BUSINESS BETWEEN US...

18:56.831 --> 18:59.050
SEEMS LIKE
AN EMPTY TRICK.

18:59.094 --> 19:00.487
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:00.530 --> 19:04.795
SOMETHING I LEARNED
THE HARD WAY...

19:04.839 --> 19:06.057
WHENEVER I'M WITH SOMEONE

19:06.101 --> 19:07.581
THE MORE I BEGIN
TO FEEL...

19:07.624 --> 19:08.843
- INADEQUATE?
- NEVER!

19:08.886 --> 19:09.844
- TONGUE-TIED?
- NO.

19:09.887 --> 19:11.193
- AROUSED?
- YE--

19:11.237 --> 19:14.718
I'M JUST SAYING...

19:14.762 --> 19:16.633
THE MORE
I'M INTO SOMEBODY

19:16.677 --> 19:20.246
THE GREATER THE ODDS
THAT IT'S GONNA END BADLY.

19:20.289 --> 19:24.206
AND BASED ON THAT,
HOW WOULD WE END?

19:24.250 --> 19:29.820
EXTREMELY BADLY.

19:29.864 --> 19:31.561
YOU HEAR
WHAT I JUST SAID?

19:31.605 --> 19:33.998
Narrator:
THIS WAS THE FIRST TIME
THE PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR

19:34.042 --> 19:35.261
HAD EVER BEEN ORDERED TO...

19:35.304 --> 19:36.479
[ CLICK ]

19:36.523 --> 19:39.178
COME.

19:41.354 --> 19:42.920
[ BARKING ]

19:42.964 --> 19:44.531
[ CLICK ]

19:44.574 --> 19:46.837
Narrator: AS EMERSON
WENT AGAINST WHAT HE WAS SURE

19:46.881 --> 19:48.752
WAS HIS BETTER JUDGMENT

19:48.796 --> 19:51.407
CHUCK AND OLIVE DID THE SAME

19:51.451 --> 19:54.845
BY PAYING A VISIT
TO NED'S FATHER.

19:54.889 --> 19:55.933
PIE DELIVERY!

19:55.977 --> 19:57.283
SURPRISE RANDOM
PIE DELIVERY!

19:57.326 --> 19:58.632
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]
Man: JUST A MINUTE.

19:58.675 --> 20:00.329
THIS IS A GOOD IDEA. RIGHT?

20:00.373 --> 20:02.113
SOUNDED LIKE A GOOD IDEA
WHEN YOU DESCRIBED IT TO ME.

20:02.157 --> 20:04.072
YEAH, IMAGINE IF WE'D HAVE
DRAGGED NED HERE AND FOUND OUT

20:04.115 --> 20:05.639
THAT HIS DAD'S STILL
AN EMOTIONAL DISASTER?

20:05.682 --> 20:07.293
AND IT TURNS OUT
HE'S OLDER AND CRANKIER

20:07.336 --> 20:09.120
AND DRINKS $6 BOTTLES
OF SOUR MASH?

20:09.164 --> 20:11.427
OHH, NED WOULD HAVE A TRUMP CARD
OF AN I-TOLD-YA-SO.

20:11.471 --> 20:14.474
Man: COME IN!

20:14.517 --> 20:16.693
HI!

20:16.737 --> 20:18.391
IT'LL TAKE JUST A MINUTE.

20:18.434 --> 20:21.263
WAIT WE'RE ACTUALY LOOKING
FOR AN OLDER...

20:21.307 --> 20:25.311
OH. O-OKAY. ALRIGHT.

20:25.354 --> 20:26.529
VOILA!

20:26.573 --> 20:27.617
OH.

20:27.661 --> 20:29.880
OH, THANK YOU.

20:29.924 --> 20:30.881
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:31.621 --> 20:33.362
[ KNOCKING ]

20:36.060 --> 20:37.279
IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

20:37.323 --> 20:38.672
THE STUPID FALSE BOTTOM
KEEPS JAMMING.

20:38.715 --> 20:39.890
IT WORKS WHEN I DO IT.

20:39.934 --> 20:43.459
OH, TWINS!
OH, I LOVE TWINS!

20:43.503 --> 20:45.461
I-I'M RALSTON.
THIS IS MAURICE.

20:45.505 --> 20:46.767
WE HAVE A BIG SHOW
COMING UP.

20:46.810 --> 20:47.898
OH, ACTUALLY, WE WERE LOOKING

20:47.942 --> 20:49.639
FOR AN OLDER MAN
THAT LIVES HERE?

20:49.683 --> 20:51.728
HE WON A PIE IN A RAFFLE.
WE HAVE A RAFFLE EVERY WEEK.

20:51.772 --> 20:52.990
IT'S VERY EXCITING.

20:53.034 --> 20:54.383
THE ONLY OLDER MAN
WAS OUR DAD

20:54.427 --> 20:55.645
AND HE HASN'T LIVED HERE
FOR A WHILE.

20:55.689 --> 20:57.125
DID YOU SAY..."DAD"?

20:57.168 --> 21:00.084
YEAH. HE HASN'T LIVED HERE
IN A FEW YEARS.

21:00.128 --> 21:01.869
HE KINDA...
DISAPPEARED.

21:01.912 --> 21:03.174
THEN OUR MOM SHACKED UP
WITH SOMEONE ELSE

21:03.218 --> 21:04.741
SO WE KEPT THE HOUSE.

21:04.785 --> 21:07.657
Narrator: IT WAS THEN
THAT CHUCK AND OLIVE REALIZED...

21:07.701 --> 21:09.529
YOU HAVE THE SAME
EYEBROWS AS HIM!

21:09.572 --> 21:11.618
THEY DO!
THEY DO!

21:11.661 --> 21:13.228
I SAID THAT TWICE --
ONCE FOR EACH OF YOU.

21:13.272 --> 21:14.534
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:14.577 --> 21:16.623
YOU HAVE SEEN TWINS
BEFORE, RIGHT?

21:16.666 --> 21:18.364
OH, YEAH.
SHE DIDN'T MEAN THE SAME
AS EACH OTHER. SHE MEANT...

21:18.407 --> 21:20.148
Narrator:
A PAUSE AS THEY CONSIDERED

21:20.191 --> 21:21.845
HOW THE PIE MAKER MIGHT REACT

21:21.889 --> 21:24.021
IF HE KNEW THEY HAD DISCOVERED
HIS HALF-BROTHERS.

21:24.065 --> 21:25.588
DAD MUST BE
VERY HANDSOME.

21:25.632 --> 21:27.851
OH, YEAH.
ENJOY THE PIE.
Both: THANKS.

21:27.895 --> 21:29.636
BYE.

21:29.679 --> 21:30.854
[ INDISTINCT ARGUING ]

21:33.379 --> 21:35.337
Narrator:
SIMONE COME AND GONE

21:35.381 --> 21:37.165
EMERSON FELT FLUSHED

21:37.208 --> 21:39.341
WITH A POST-COITAL SENSE
OF ACHIEVEMENT

21:39.385 --> 21:42.170
AND RENEWED POWERS
OF MENTAL CLARITY.

21:42.213 --> 21:43.911
HE SPOTTED SOMETHING.

21:43.954 --> 21:48.089
WHO ARE YOU,
BUSBOY IN EVERY PICTURE?

21:48.132 --> 21:50.961
Narrator:
AND LOOKING MORE CLOSELY...

21:51.005 --> 21:52.528
[ DIALING ]

21:52.572 --> 21:55.357
MEET ME AT THE DIM SUM.

21:58.926 --> 22:01.363
THREE REASONS I WANT TO SPEAK
TO THAT BUSBOY.

22:01.407 --> 22:03.539
ONE, HE MAKES $5 AN HOUR

22:03.583 --> 22:07.761
AND HE'S WEARING A $2,300
OMEGA DeVILLE PRESTIGE
QUARTZ WRISTWATCH.

22:07.804 --> 22:09.980
TWO, HE'S ALWAYS HANGING
AROUND THAT POKER TABLE.

22:10.024 --> 22:13.375
AND, THREE, HE'S BEEN WATCHING
US EVER SINCE WE CAME IN HERE.

22:13.419 --> 22:15.377
SINCE WE CAME HERE.
WHERE WERE YOU?

22:15.421 --> 22:16.683
GAMBLING. FOR YOU.

22:16.726 --> 22:18.293
AND I HIT A JACKPOT --

22:18.337 --> 22:21.470
BUT, UM, MAYBE NOT
THE KIND YOU'D LIKE.

22:21.514 --> 22:22.950
WHAT OTHER KIND IS THERE?

22:22.993 --> 22:25.474
BUSBOY'S MAKING A RUN FOR IT.
LET'S GO.

22:25.518 --> 22:27.650
HOW COULD YOU GO TO MY DAD'S
HOUSE WITHOUT TELLING ME?

22:27.694 --> 22:29.130
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
YOU HAVE BROTHERS.

22:29.173 --> 22:30.697
HALF-BROTHERS.

22:30.740 --> 22:32.568
TWO HALF-BROTHERS,
WHICH IS LIKE ONE WHOLE ONE

22:32.612 --> 22:34.004
AND, ANYWAY,
THEY'RE FAMILY

22:34.048 --> 22:36.703
AND YOUR DAD DID
THE SAME THING TO THEM.

22:36.746 --> 22:39.096
AND, NED, THEY HAVE
YOUR EYEBROWS

22:39.140 --> 22:40.881
AND THEY DO PARLOR MAGIC!

22:40.924 --> 22:42.926
SO, MAURICE,
HE JUMPS INTO ONE TRUNK

22:42.970 --> 22:44.319
AND THEN RALSTON JUMPS OUT
OF THE OTHER ONE.

22:44.363 --> 22:46.408
"MAURICE" AND "RALSTON"?

22:46.452 --> 22:47.801
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THEIR NAMES?

22:47.844 --> 22:49.759
I'M GLAD DAD GOT SO FUN
AND CREATIVE WITH NAMING

22:49.803 --> 22:51.282
AFTER I LEFT.

22:51.326 --> 22:53.981
GOODBYE, NED.
HELLO, MERCUTIO AND RIBALD!

22:54.024 --> 22:55.983
MAURICE AND RALSTON!

22:56.026 --> 22:57.724
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
IN A SECOND MARRIAGE.

22:57.767 --> 23:00.291
PEOPLE LOOSEN UP, DROP THEIR
BAGGAGE, AND LIVE A LITTLE.

23:00.335 --> 23:02.642
- OOH.
- I WAS THE BAGGAGE.

23:02.685 --> 23:03.817
UGH.

23:03.860 --> 23:06.950
BUSBOY'S NOT IN THE KITCHEN.

23:06.994 --> 23:08.430
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.

23:08.474 --> 23:09.997
YEAH, RIGHT, OVER THERE.

23:10.040 --> 23:13.435
AHA! OHH. OHH.

23:13.479 --> 23:15.959
THIS IS WHERE BAO WORKED
HIS MAGIC.

23:16.003 --> 23:18.222
IT'S TERRIBLE YOUR DAD LEFT YOU.
IT'S NOT YOUR BROTHERS' FAULT.

23:18.266 --> 23:19.485
IT'S NOT EVEN HALF
THEIR FAULT.

23:19.528 --> 23:21.443
WHY NOT TRY TO GET
TO KNOW THEM?

23:21.487 --> 23:24.490
I KNOW OTHER NICE PEOPLE MY
FATHER DIDN'T ABANDON ME FOR.

23:24.533 --> 23:27.014
[ GROANING ]

23:27.057 --> 23:28.581
OH, NO, TOO MUCH PRESSURE.

23:28.624 --> 23:31.061
NO, THIS ISN'T GOOD!
WHAT IS THAT?

23:31.105 --> 23:35.239
THAT IS A NEWLY REPAIRED
BUN STEAMER!

23:35.283 --> 23:37.154
WATCH OUT!

23:44.205 --> 23:45.206
Man: AAH!

23:45.249 --> 23:46.250
WHO SHRIEKED?

23:46.294 --> 23:48.949
I MIGHT HAVE SHRIEKED.

23:48.992 --> 23:52.431
IT SOUNDED LIKE IT CAME
FROM OVER THERE.

23:52.474 --> 23:53.823
I THINK I FOUND HIM.

23:53.867 --> 23:56.565
IT'S THE BUSBOY.

23:56.609 --> 23:57.697
MM-HMM.

23:57.740 --> 23:59.046
YOU THINK JUST
'CAUSE YOU DEAD

23:59.089 --> 24:00.482
YOU AIN'T GONNA TELL US
WHAT YOU WAS UP TO

24:00.526 --> 24:02.615
BUT YOU ARE SO WRONG.

24:12.886 --> 24:13.930
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

24:13.974 --> 24:15.584
WHAT THE HELL'S THAT?

24:15.628 --> 24:18.021
I believe it's a three-foot
length of copper pipe.

24:18.065 --> 24:20.502
I wonder if that's excluded
under "Special Circumstances."

24:20.546 --> 24:21.808
What "Special Circumstance"?

24:21.851 --> 24:23.505
MY LIFE INSURANCE POLICY.

24:23.549 --> 24:25.289
THAT'S WHAT I DO --
INVESTIGATE POLICY CLAIMS.

24:25.333 --> 24:27.509
I'M PERRY LONG
WITH DAWSON & STUBBS...

24:27.553 --> 24:29.293
PREVIOUSLY.

24:29.337 --> 24:31.948
Well, Perry, judging by the
man-made crimp in the pipe

24:31.992 --> 24:33.776
I think we looking
at your garden-variety

24:33.820 --> 24:34.951
premeditated murder.

24:34.995 --> 24:37.650
Nice!
It's a solid payout.

24:37.693 --> 24:38.999
Listen, if you're
an insurance investigator

24:39.042 --> 24:40.783
what the hell you doing
posing as a busboy?

24:40.827 --> 24:42.176
WORKING UNDERCOVER.

24:42.219 --> 24:43.525
CHECKING OUT
A SUSPICIOUS POLICY CLAIM

24:43.569 --> 24:45.135
BY A CHEF NAMED BAO TING.

24:45.179 --> 24:46.528
We know Bao.

24:46.572 --> 24:48.878
BAO TOOK OUT A $200,000
LIFE INSURANCE POLICY

24:48.922 --> 24:50.401
ONE DAY BEFORE HE DIED.

24:50.445 --> 24:51.446
WHAT ARE WE, IDIOTS?

24:51.490 --> 24:52.491
WHO'S THE BENEFICIARY?

24:52.534 --> 24:54.536
HIS DAUGHTER.

24:54.580 --> 24:57.234
NAME'S MEI.
SHE WORKS AT THE RESTAURANT.

24:57.278 --> 25:00.455
THANKS, PERRY.

25:00.499 --> 25:02.022
YOU THINK HE LEFT ME MONEY?

25:02.065 --> 25:04.372
I'LL BELIEVE IT WHEN I SEE IT.

25:04.415 --> 25:06.505
WELL, 200 GRAND'S
A LOT OF DOUGH.

25:06.548 --> 25:08.376
MAYBE ENOUGH FOR SOMEBODY
WHO FELT IGNORED

25:08.419 --> 25:10.117
AND NEGLECTED TO CASH IN?

25:10.160 --> 25:12.815
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME?
I HAVE A TABLE WAITING.

25:12.859 --> 25:15.992
WAIT, WAIT.
HOLD ON A SECOND. I --

25:16.036 --> 25:17.820
SINCE I'M WAITING
ON AN ORDER

25:17.864 --> 25:19.692
MAYBE YOU OUGHT TO LET HER
DO HER JOB.

25:19.735 --> 25:24.566
- YES. GOOD IDEA.
- YEAH, YOU RIGHT.

25:24.610 --> 25:27.177
AND THAT IS SHRIMPBOY.

25:27.221 --> 25:28.614
HE RUNS THE POKER TABLE.

25:28.657 --> 25:30.441
HE DIDN'T LIKE US
TALKING TO MEI.

25:30.485 --> 25:32.008
MAYBE THEY'RE ALL
IN ON IT TOGETHER.

25:32.052 --> 25:33.140
YEAH.

25:33.183 --> 25:36.143
MR. COD?
FOOD TO-GO.

25:36.186 --> 25:39.538
I DIDN'T ORDER THIS.

25:42.236 --> 25:45.413
Narrator:
ALTHOUGH THE HANDWRITING
WAS FAMILIAR TO EMERSON

25:45.456 --> 25:48.982
AS IT TURNED OUT,
THE AUTHOR WAS A SURPRISE.

25:49.025 --> 25:51.245
YOU THINK I KILLED
MY FATHER?

25:51.288 --> 25:52.855
THEN WHY WOULD I SEND YOU
THE FORTUNE COOKIE

25:52.899 --> 25:54.422
THE FIRST TIME
ASKING FOR HELP?

25:54.465 --> 25:56.337
YOUR MOTHER SENT ME
THAT COOKIE. NO!

25:56.380 --> 25:58.469
I SENT YOU THE COOKIE

25:58.513 --> 26:01.690
KNOWING SHE WAS THERE THAT DAY
COLLECTING MY DAD'S BELONGINGS.

26:01.734 --> 26:04.214
I WANTED HER
TO RUN INTO YOU.

26:04.258 --> 26:06.347
I KNEW SHE WAS SUSPICIOUS
OF HOW DAD DIED.

26:06.390 --> 26:07.783
WHY COULDN'T YOU
JUST HIRE ME?

26:07.827 --> 26:11.047
BECAUSE SHRIMPBOY
WATCHES ME!

26:11.091 --> 26:13.093
I KNOW ALL HIS SECRETS

26:13.136 --> 26:15.269
BUT MOM DOESN'T KNOW
ANYTHING

26:15.312 --> 26:19.273
NOT EVEN
ABOUT THE GAMBLING.

26:19.316 --> 26:21.754
IF HE KNEW I WAS TALKING
TO YOU NOW...

26:21.797 --> 26:24.844
WHAT'S HE AFRAID
YOU'RE GONNA SAY?

26:24.887 --> 26:28.674
THAT I'LL TELL YOU ABOUT
THE BET MY FATHER LOST.

26:28.717 --> 26:29.936
DID YOU SAY "BET"?

26:29.979 --> 26:31.590
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

26:31.633 --> 26:33.548
CHASING MONEY
FOR HIS OWN RESTAURANT

26:33.592 --> 26:35.376
AT THE DIM SUM POKER TABLE

26:35.419 --> 26:38.553
BAO HAD GAMBLED AWAY
HIS LIFE SAVINGS.

26:38.597 --> 26:40.120
HE THEN BEGGED
THE OTHER GAMBLERS

26:40.163 --> 26:41.904
TO LET HIM PLAY ON CREDIT.

26:41.948 --> 26:44.733
SHRIMPBOY AGREED,
ON ONE CONDITION --

26:44.777 --> 26:46.648
IF BAO LOST THE NEXT HAND

26:46.692 --> 26:48.737
HIS DAUGHTER
WOULD BE FORCED TO MARRY

26:48.781 --> 26:52.132
SHRIMPBOY'S SOCIALLY
HANDICAPPED COUSIN, RUBBIE

26:52.175 --> 26:54.743
MANAGER OF THE DIM SUM.

26:54.787 --> 26:58.834
20 MINUTES LATER,
MEI WAS ENGAGED.

26:58.878 --> 27:01.576
AND SINCE SHRIMPBOY BELIEVED
THE TERMS OF A BET

27:01.620 --> 27:03.578
SHOULD BE FOLLOWED
TO THE LETTER

27:03.622 --> 27:07.756
HE KEPT A CLOSE WATCH ON MEI.

27:07.800 --> 27:09.540
IT'S THE WRONG BET.

27:09.584 --> 27:11.673
BAO GAMBLED AWAY
HIS DAUGHTER'S HAND IN MARRIAGE

27:11.717 --> 27:13.501
BUT SO FAR,
MEI'S KEPT HER END
OF THE BARGAIN.

27:13.544 --> 27:15.546
THERE'S NO MOTIVE.

27:15.590 --> 27:17.984
NO WAY SHE'S GONNA
STAY IN SOME KIND OF
AN ARRANGED MARRIAGE.

27:18.027 --> 27:19.507
SHE AIN'T GOING ANYWHERE.

27:19.550 --> 27:21.901
NOT AS LONG AS SHE'S UNDER
SHRIMPBOY'S THUMB.

27:21.944 --> 27:23.642
WE GOT TO PROVE THAT
SHRIMPBOY KILLED BAO.

27:23.685 --> 27:25.687
AND TO DO THAT, WE GOT
TO QUESTION SHRIMPBOY.

27:25.731 --> 27:27.863
BUT THERE ARE BODYGUARDS
INVOLVED --

27:27.907 --> 27:29.082
VERY BIG ONES.

27:29.125 --> 27:30.257
MAYBE SIMONE CAN HELP.

27:30.300 --> 27:31.650
SIMONE CAN'T HELP.

27:31.693 --> 27:33.129
I THOUGHT YOU TALKED TO HER.

27:33.173 --> 27:35.697
OR DID YOU MORE THAN TALK?

27:35.741 --> 27:37.351
YOU DID MORE THAN TALK.

27:37.394 --> 27:39.266
[ SMOOCHING ]

27:39.309 --> 27:40.876
WE DECIDED TO COOL
THINGS OFF

27:40.920 --> 27:42.704
AS A MUTUAL AGREEMENT
AMICABLY REACHED

27:42.748 --> 27:44.314
BY TWO HIGHLY MATURE
ADULTS!

27:44.358 --> 27:46.316
MM.

27:46.360 --> 27:48.449
EXCUSE ME.

27:48.492 --> 27:50.712
[ CHUCKLING ]

27:50.756 --> 27:53.628
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

27:53.672 --> 27:55.064
UM...

27:55.108 --> 27:57.023
I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.

27:57.066 --> 27:58.720
Olive: OOH. IS THIS AN APOLOGY

27:58.764 --> 28:00.069
FOR GOING TO NED'S DAD'S HOUSE?

28:00.113 --> 28:01.767
AND IF SO,
CAN I PLEASE GET IN ON IT?

28:01.810 --> 28:03.638
BECAUSE I, TOO,
AM VERY SORRY.

28:03.682 --> 28:05.988
I WAS THROWN THAT YOU WENT
BEHIND MY BACK TO LOOK FOR A MAN

28:06.032 --> 28:10.384
WHO MADE MY TENDER, FORMATIVE
YEARS PURE MISERY.

28:10.427 --> 28:12.647
THAT SAID,
I APPRECIATE THE APOLOGY.

28:12.691 --> 28:13.866
WELL, WE WEREN'T
GONNA TELL YOU ANYTHING

28:13.909 --> 28:15.432
IF WE DIDN'T HAVE
GOOD NEWS.

28:15.476 --> 28:17.521
YOUR BROTHERS ARE FRIENDLY
AND VERY CUTE --

28:17.565 --> 28:18.958
NOT THAT YOU CARE
ABOUT THAT

28:19.001 --> 28:21.003
BUT I THOUGHT IT QUALIFIED
AS GOOD NEWS.

28:21.047 --> 28:22.439
ESPECIALLY THE "BROTHERS"
AND THE "FRIENDLY" PART.

28:22.483 --> 28:23.876
YEAH, AND IT WAS WRONG
TO BE SNEAKY.

28:23.919 --> 28:25.616
I WAS TRYING
NOT TO BE PUSHY

28:25.660 --> 28:29.185
AND REPLACING "SNEAKY"
WITH "PUSHY" WAS A BIG MISTAKE

28:29.229 --> 28:30.709
- BUT...
- "BUT?"

28:30.752 --> 28:32.145
BUT I KNOW YOU.

28:32.188 --> 28:33.320
YOU SAY YOU DON'T WANT
TO FEEL CONNECTED

28:33.363 --> 28:35.191
BUT I DON'T BELIEVE THAT.

28:35.235 --> 28:36.802
I MEAN, EVERYONE NEEDS FAMILY.

28:36.845 --> 28:39.282
YOU'RE MY FAMILY.

28:39.326 --> 28:41.632
AND YOU TO A SLIGHTLY
LESSER DEGREE.

28:41.676 --> 28:44.766
THANKS.
TO A SLIGHTLY LESSER DEGREE.

28:44.810 --> 28:47.247
I'VE SPENT MY LIFE NOT HAVING
THINGS IN COMMON WITH MY FATHER

28:47.290 --> 28:48.727
WHICH IS A GOOD THING.

28:48.770 --> 28:50.467
BUT IF I REACH OUT
TO MY BROTHERS

28:50.511 --> 28:53.253
I'M BETTING IT'LL MAKE MY DAD
FEEL GOOD, WHEREVER HE IS.

28:53.296 --> 28:54.907
I DON'T WANT THAT.

28:54.950 --> 28:58.432
IF THAT SEEMS PETTY
AND VINDICTIVE AND SMALL

28:58.475 --> 29:00.042
THINK OF IT AS AN HOMAGE
TO MY FATHER

29:00.086 --> 29:02.218
AND THE TINY PART OF US
THAT IS THE SAME.

29:02.262 --> 29:04.525
Narrator: AS CHUCK AND OLIVE
PONDERED THE DISTANCE

29:04.568 --> 29:07.746
NED PUT BETWEEN HIMSELF
AND HIS PAST

29:07.789 --> 29:12.402
EMERSON PONDERED WAYS OF GETTING
CLOSER TO SHRIMPBOY.

29:12.446 --> 29:14.970
WHILE TRACKING THE POTENTIALLY
MURDEROUS GANGSTER

29:15.014 --> 29:17.233
THE P.I. CAME UP
AGAINST SOMETHING

29:17.277 --> 29:19.192
FAR MORE FRIGHTENING --

29:19.235 --> 29:21.020
SIMONE.

29:21.063 --> 29:24.371
THE MUTUAL DECISION
TO LET THINGS "COOL OFF"

29:24.414 --> 29:27.026
HAD NOT, IN FACT, BEEN MUTUAL.

29:27.069 --> 29:29.768
BUT AS HE GAZED UP AT THE STARS

29:29.811 --> 29:34.163
HIS THOUGHTS TURNED TO HIS
FAVORITE WARM, PUFFY PASTRIES

29:34.207 --> 29:37.601
AND THE DELICIOUS SURPRISES
HIDDEN INSIDE.

29:37.645 --> 29:40.996
AND THEN HE GOT AN IDEA.

30:01.060 --> 30:02.539
[ GONG CLANGS ]

30:05.978 --> 30:07.893
Narrator: EMERSON'S PLAN
INVOLVED A POT OF GREEN TEA

30:07.936 --> 30:10.765
AND CHINESE HERBS
WHICH MEI HAD SUPPLIED.

30:10.809 --> 30:13.812
WHEN INGESTED,
THE HERBS WERE KNOWN TO CAUSE

30:13.855 --> 30:18.120
AN UNCOMFORTABLE FULLNESS
OF THE BLADDER.

30:18.164 --> 30:20.688
[ SPEAKING MANDARIN ]

30:20.731 --> 30:22.559
[ DISHES CLINKING ]

30:28.957 --> 30:30.829
LITTLE COUSIN WINS AGAIN.

30:30.872 --> 30:34.833
HOW 'BOUT THAT, HUH?

30:34.876 --> 30:37.966
BOSS, I GOT AN UNCOMFORTABLE
FULLNESS OF THE BLADDER.

30:38.010 --> 30:40.621
YEAH, ME -- ME TOO.

30:40.664 --> 30:42.797
[ SPEAKING MANDARIN ]

30:55.201 --> 30:58.378
[ WHISTLING ]

30:58.421 --> 31:00.206
I'M SORRY, WE'RE CLOSING.

31:00.249 --> 31:02.773
WHAT IF I SAID WE WAS HERE
FOR THE "HAO SHOU YUN" SPECIAL?

31:02.817 --> 31:04.993
SAME FOR ME, DARLIN'.

31:05.037 --> 31:05.994
THAT'S RIGHT.

31:06.038 --> 31:07.387
WHAT'S UP, PLAYERS?

31:07.430 --> 31:09.041
WHICH ONE OF Y'ALL
BE SHRIMPBOY?

31:09.084 --> 31:11.043
DEPENDS. WHO'S ASKING?

31:11.086 --> 31:12.566
"WHO'S ASKING"
IS JIMMY THE ACE.

31:12.609 --> 31:13.872
RICKY THE HAMMER
WILL VOUCH FOR ME.

31:13.915 --> 31:15.090
WE DID TIME
IN THE JOINT TOGETHER.

31:15.134 --> 31:16.700
WHERE IS RICKY,
THAT LOVABLE CUTTHROAT?

31:16.744 --> 31:20.226
NEVER HEARD OF HIM.
AND THIS GAME...IS FULL.

31:20.269 --> 31:22.576
Yeah, well, uh
[clears throat]
that's too bad,

31:22.619 --> 31:24.534
'cause, uh,
the sucker behind me

31:24.578 --> 31:27.102
got pockets so deep,
he write a check
and the bank bounce.

31:27.146 --> 31:28.887
He's a Grade-A fish.

31:28.930 --> 31:33.152
I thought I'd bring him
in here so we can
pick him clean.

31:33.195 --> 31:35.632
RUBBIE, WHY DON'T YOU
AND LOUIE SIT THIS ONE OUT?

31:35.676 --> 31:39.898
YES, RUBBIE.

31:39.941 --> 31:41.464
HAVE A SEAT, PLAYER.

31:41.508 --> 31:43.945
IT'S A GRAND BUY-IN.
HOPE THAT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

31:43.989 --> 31:49.211
OH, I ALWAYS CARRY AROUND
SOME LOOSE CHANGE.

31:49.255 --> 31:50.865
[ SIGHS ]

31:50.909 --> 31:52.258
[ GRUNTS ]

31:52.301 --> 31:55.435
DAMN, WOMAN,
YOU GOT THE KUNG FU GRIP.

32:01.920 --> 32:04.183
AIN'T YOU THE SHRIMPBOY
WON HIMSELF A BRIDE
IN A POKER GAME?

32:04.226 --> 32:05.749
I HEARD ABOUT THAT.

32:05.793 --> 32:08.274
I THOUGHT, "THAT FELLA
NEEDS TO GET OUT MORE.

32:08.317 --> 32:10.015
THERE'S BETTER WAYS
TO MEET GIRLS."

32:10.058 --> 32:12.147
[ LAUGHS LOUDLY ]

32:12.931 --> 32:14.367
EH.

32:14.410 --> 32:17.196
I WAS PLAYING HER DAD.
GIRL WASN'T FOR ME.

32:17.239 --> 32:19.024
SEE, MY COUSIN AIN'T TOO HOT
WITH THE LADIES

32:19.067 --> 32:20.416
SO I DID HIM A FAVOR.

32:20.460 --> 32:21.983
YEAH, I BET HER DADDY
WAS PRETTY ANGRY

32:22.027 --> 32:24.203
WHEN HE LOST THAT BET,
HUH? [ CHUCKLES ]

32:24.246 --> 32:27.075
WELL, IF HE WAS, WHY'D HE PLAY
THE HAND IN THE FIRST PLACE?

32:27.119 --> 32:30.644
SEE, AROUND HERE,
A BET'S SACRED.

32:30.687 --> 32:33.212
YOUR WORD IS ALL YOU GOT.

32:39.435 --> 32:41.568
BET'S TO YOU, NEW GUY.

32:41.611 --> 32:43.874
$300 TO STAY IN.

32:43.918 --> 32:46.486
OH, IS THAT ALL?
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:46.529 --> 32:47.835
YOU CAN RAISE.

32:47.878 --> 32:49.315
UH, NO, I LIKE TO BEGIN

32:49.358 --> 32:51.708
WITH AN INSIGNIFICANT SUM,
LIKE THIS

32:51.752 --> 32:54.624
AND THEN WORK MY WAY UP
TO THE REAL MONEY.

32:54.668 --> 32:56.191
YEAH, SPEAKING
OF REAL MONEY --

32:56.235 --> 32:57.627
IF I WAS YOU

32:57.671 --> 32:59.890
I'D HAVE KEPT RIGHT ON
BETTING WITH THAT FOOL.

32:59.934 --> 33:01.022
HE SOUND LIKE
AN EASY MARK.

33:01.066 --> 33:02.023
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:02.067 --> 33:03.807
OH, HE CAME BACK

33:03.851 --> 33:06.549
FELT GUILTY ABOUT HIS DAUGHTER
HAVING TO MARRY MY COUSIN.

33:06.593 --> 33:08.551
SAID HE WANTED TO WIN
HER FREEDOM BACK.

33:08.595 --> 33:10.379
SO IT WASN'T ABOUT MONEY
THIS PARTICULAR TIME.

33:10.423 --> 33:12.468
HE WAS JUST TRYING
TO HELP HIS DAUGHTER.

33:12.512 --> 33:14.035
EXCEPT HE HAD NOTHING
TO BET WITH.

33:14.079 --> 33:15.732
SO I TOLD HIM TO GET LOST.

33:15.776 --> 33:17.647
YO, YOU IN OR WHAT?

33:17.691 --> 33:19.736
OH, YEAH, YEAH.

33:19.780 --> 33:23.653
ALRIGHT.
LET'S SWITCH 'EM.

33:23.697 --> 33:24.741
[ POUNDING ON DOOR ]

33:24.785 --> 33:26.047
Man:
HEY, SOMEBODY!

33:26.091 --> 33:27.135
Man #2: OPEN UP!

33:27.179 --> 33:30.269
[ MUFFLED SHOUTING ]

33:30.312 --> 33:33.011
[ GONG CLANGING ]

33:33.054 --> 33:34.447
KEEP WALKIN'.

33:34.490 --> 33:36.666
I LOVE GONGS!
NOTHING WRONG WITH THAT.

33:36.710 --> 33:38.581
[ CLANGING CONTINUES ]

33:38.625 --> 33:41.062
Narrator: THE BODYGUARDS
STILL INDISPOSED

33:41.106 --> 33:44.805
THE PRIVATE INVESTIGATORS
CONSIDERED THEIR LATEST CLUE --

33:44.848 --> 33:47.068
THAT THE BET
THAT HAD GOTTEN BAO KILLED

33:47.112 --> 33:50.419
HAD NOT BEEN WITH SHRIMPBOY
AFTER ALL

33:50.463 --> 33:52.204
BUT WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

33:52.247 --> 33:54.075
Bao wanted to win back
Mei's freedom.

33:54.119 --> 33:55.903
If Shrimpboy
wouldn't play

33:55.946 --> 33:58.079
there's always someone else
Bao could have played against.

33:58.123 --> 33:59.211
You mean Rubbie?

33:59.254 --> 34:00.690
Yeah.

34:00.734 --> 34:02.736
Bao would've gone
directly to her fiance

34:02.779 --> 34:06.087
to try to win Mei
back from him.

34:06.131 --> 34:08.046
HEY. TIME TO PUT UP
OR SHUT UP.

34:08.089 --> 34:09.090
OH, YEAH, YEAH.

34:09.134 --> 34:10.396
YEAH.

34:10.439 --> 34:12.746
LET'S DO THIS.

34:15.966 --> 34:18.099
PORK BUNS,
SHRIMP DUMPLINGS

34:18.143 --> 34:19.753
FULL HOUSE.

34:19.796 --> 34:22.843
BEEF POT STICKERS,
STRAIGHT TO THE NINE.

34:22.886 --> 34:25.802
Bao had life insurance.
What if he gambled that?

34:25.846 --> 34:27.543
I mean,
Mei's the beneficiary

34:27.587 --> 34:29.589
but if Rubbie marries her,
then he gets the money.

34:29.632 --> 34:32.070
And Rubbie wouldn't collect
as long as Bao was alive.

34:32.113 --> 34:34.159
Narrator: AT LAST,
THE TRUTH WAS CLEAR.

34:34.202 --> 34:35.595
Rubbie murdered Bao.

34:35.638 --> 34:38.119
BEEF AND STICKY BUNS --
EMPTY. YOU BLUFF.

34:38.163 --> 34:39.512
We better hurry up
and finish this business

34:39.555 --> 34:41.122
and then call the police.

34:41.166 --> 34:44.473
WHAT'S WITH THE WHISPERING?
SHOW THE DAMN CARDS.

34:44.517 --> 34:48.390
OH, YEAH.

34:48.434 --> 34:49.435
10 HIGH.

34:49.478 --> 34:51.045
[ LAUGHTER ]

34:51.089 --> 34:54.440
SHRIMP DUMPLINGS,
FOUR OF A KIND.

34:54.483 --> 34:55.963
WINNING HAND.

34:56.006 --> 34:57.617
I WON?

34:57.660 --> 35:02.187
YEAH, I WON!
[ LAUGHS ]

35:02.230 --> 35:04.754
TIME TO CASH OUT.

35:11.413 --> 35:13.372
OW! HAVE TO BE SO TIGHT?

35:13.415 --> 35:15.330
I GOT BAD CIRCULATION.

35:15.374 --> 35:19.160
KEEP THEM HERE UNTIL ME
AND MY FIANCE ARE ON THE PLANE.

35:19.204 --> 35:20.727
WE'RE TAKING
OUR HONEYMOON EARLY.

35:20.770 --> 35:22.381
RIGHT, HONEY?

35:22.424 --> 35:24.687
HEY, CRAB CAKE, YOU HELP HIM,
YOU'RE AN ACCESSORY

35:24.731 --> 35:26.385
AND I'M NOT TALKING
GUCCI HANDBAG.

35:26.428 --> 35:27.908
I'M TALKING HARD TIME
IN THE PEN

35:27.951 --> 35:30.737
THE JOINT, THE HOOSEGOW,
THE FORBIDDEN CITY.

35:30.780 --> 35:33.261
MY COUSIN WON A BET,
AND AROUND HERE...

35:33.305 --> 35:36.525
A BET IS SACRED.

35:36.569 --> 35:38.875
WHAT? I'M...JUST
REPEATING WHAT HE SAID.

35:38.919 --> 35:40.877
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

35:40.921 --> 35:43.053
BAO'S DESPERATE PLEA
FOR A CHANCE

35:43.097 --> 35:44.751
TO WIN HIS DAUGHTER'S FREEDOM

35:44.794 --> 35:47.841
WAS PAIRED WITH AN UNFORTUNATE
LACK OF FUNDS.

35:47.884 --> 35:49.669
WHEN SHRIMPBOY REFUSED

35:49.712 --> 35:53.020
RUBBIE SUGGESTED BAO
SIMPLY WAGER THE PAYOUT

35:53.063 --> 35:55.196
FROM A LIFE INSURANCE POLICY.

35:55.240 --> 35:56.980
IF RUBBIE WON THE HAND

35:57.024 --> 35:59.853
HE WOULD MARRY MEI
AND WAIT FOR BAO TO DIE

35:59.896 --> 36:01.507
BEFORE CLAIMING HIS REWARD.

36:01.550 --> 36:05.554
RUBBIE WON THE POKER GAME
WITH AN AMAZING STRAIGHT FLUSH.

36:05.598 --> 36:09.776
BAO HAD FAILED HIS DAUGHTER
AND WAS DEVASTATED.

36:09.819 --> 36:13.345
EVEN MORE DEVASTATING
WAS BAO'S NEXT REALIZATION

36:13.388 --> 36:16.217
THAT HIS FUTURE SON-IN-LAW
DEMANDED PAYMENT...

36:16.261 --> 36:18.045
IMMEDIATELY.

36:18.088 --> 36:19.351
[ EXPLOSION ]

36:19.394 --> 36:21.831
PAPA WAS RISKING
HIS LIFE FOR ME.

36:21.875 --> 36:23.920
I WOULDN'T EVEN SPEAK TO HIM.

36:23.964 --> 36:25.705
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

36:25.748 --> 36:27.663
I THOUGHT I KNEW
MY FATHER

36:27.707 --> 36:29.404
BUT I DIDN'T KNOW HIM AT ALL.

36:29.448 --> 36:31.014
Narrator:
IT STRUCK THE PIE MAKER

36:31.058 --> 36:34.192
HE'D ALWAYS BELIEVED
HIS FATHER'S ACTIONS

36:34.235 --> 36:35.932
SPOKE FOR THEMSELVES.

36:35.976 --> 36:38.457
BUT MAYBE HE WAS WRONG.

36:38.500 --> 36:41.808
SPEAK OF THE DEVIL.

36:41.851 --> 36:43.201
SIMONE?

36:43.244 --> 36:45.246
NOBODY LOCKED THE DOOR?

36:45.290 --> 36:46.856
I DON'T THINK THIS WOULD BE
THE BEST TIME.

36:46.900 --> 36:48.510
AND WHEN WOULD BE
THE BEST TIME?

36:48.554 --> 36:49.990
CERTAINLY NOT EARLIER
WHEN YOU DIVED INTO YOUR CAR

36:50.033 --> 36:51.731
TO HIDE FROM ME.

36:51.774 --> 36:53.385
NO, SEE,
YOU DON'T UNDERST--
[ CLICKER CLICKS ]

36:53.428 --> 36:55.691
I REQUIRE HONESTY, LOYALTY,
AND RESPECT --

36:55.735 --> 36:57.127
QUALITIES YOU'VE DONE
AN EXTRAORDINARY JOB

36:57.171 --> 36:58.390
OF NOT SHOWING.

36:58.433 --> 36:59.956
SO LET'S TRY
A NEW SET OF RULES.

37:00.000 --> 37:02.045
FROM NOW ON,
YOU WILL NOT SPEAK TO ME...

37:02.089 --> 37:03.046
- BUT I --
- OR CALL ME.

37:03.090 --> 37:04.047
BUT I --
[ CLICK ]

37:04.091 --> 37:05.527
...OR COME WITHIN 20 FEET.

37:05.571 --> 37:08.530
- BUT I --
- AND STOP CALLING ME "BUT I."

37:08.574 --> 37:11.054
[ GUNS COCK ]
LADY.

37:12.534 --> 37:15.842
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:15.885 --> 37:17.409
WE HAVE A PLANE TO CATCH.

37:17.452 --> 37:19.062
NO! NO!

37:19.106 --> 37:20.281
[ BARKS ]

37:20.325 --> 37:22.892
BUBBLEGUM, STOP BEGGING!

37:22.936 --> 37:24.677
DO YOU HAVE FOOD
IN YOUR POCKET?

37:24.720 --> 37:26.156
NO.

37:26.200 --> 37:27.288
YOU DO, DON'T YOU?

37:27.332 --> 37:28.985
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

37:29.029 --> 37:31.205
I WAS WAITING ON YOU
WHEN YOU BEAT SHRIMPBOY
AT POKER.

37:31.249 --> 37:33.947
AND I BET YOU BEAT HIM BECAUSE
YOU HAD THE WINNING PORK BUN

37:33.990 --> 37:35.035
IN YOUR POCKET.

37:35.078 --> 37:36.428
YOU'RE A CHEATER.

37:36.471 --> 37:37.690
CHEATER, CHEATER,
CHEATER, CHEATER.

37:37.733 --> 37:39.431
CH-CHEATER!

37:39.474 --> 37:41.650
YEAH, AND YOU KNOW HE WAS
CHEATING WHEN HE PLAYED BAO.

37:41.694 --> 37:46.351
AND AROUND HERE,
A BET IS SACRED. RIGHT?

37:46.394 --> 37:49.876
OUT OF MY WAY!

37:49.919 --> 37:52.313
Narrator: WHILE THERE WERE
THINGS SHRIMPBOY COULD FORGIVE

37:52.357 --> 37:55.273
SUCH AS HOMICIDE, KIDNAPPING,
AND ILLEGAL POKER,

37:55.316 --> 37:59.625
HE DREW THE LINE AT CHEATING.

37:59.668 --> 38:01.366
IN PART

38:01.409 --> 38:04.020
IT WAS THE COUNTLESS HANDS
OF POKER HE'D LOST TO RUBBIE

38:04.064 --> 38:09.852
IN THE YEARS SINCE CHILDHOOD,
NOW SEEN IN A DIFFERENT LIGHT.

38:09.896 --> 38:11.898
AS RUBBIE HAD CHEATED BAO

38:11.941 --> 38:14.814
SHRIMPBOY AGREED
THE BET WAS NON BINDING.

38:14.857 --> 38:17.338
MEI AND HER FRIENDS
WERE FREE TO GO.

38:17.382 --> 38:19.209
AND MEI'S ENGAGEMENT
WAS DISENGAGED.

38:19.253 --> 38:20.994
AH, SPARKLY.

38:21.037 --> 38:24.040
BECAUSE SHRIMPBOY BELIEVED
THAT ALL GAMES ARE MEANINGLESS

38:24.084 --> 38:27.043
UNLESS WE RISK SOMETHING REAL.

38:27.087 --> 38:29.437
RUBBIE RISKED SOMETHING REAL

38:29.481 --> 38:32.092
AND WHAT HE GAINED,
AS OLIVE PREDICTED

38:32.135 --> 38:34.964
WAS A VISIT TO THE HOOSEGOW.

38:35.008 --> 38:38.707
AFTER THE INSURANCE COMPANY MADE
A GRUDGING PAYOUT TO MEI

38:38.751 --> 38:42.015
SHE SHARED IT WITH HER MOTHER,
WHO SHARED IT WITH EMERSON --

38:42.058 --> 38:45.888
PAYMENT FOR A JOB WELL DONE.

38:45.932 --> 38:49.152
STILL, EMERSON WAS FORCED
TO ACKNOWLEDGE

38:49.196 --> 38:51.590
IT HAD BEEN A JOB
NOT SO WELL DONE

38:51.633 --> 38:57.509
WHERE SIMONE WAS CONCERNED.

38:57.552 --> 38:59.728
SIMONE! SIMONE!
[ CLICK ]

39:00.686 --> 39:02.688
DAMN IT, WOMAN!

39:02.731 --> 39:04.603
WHATEVER IT IS,
SAY IT QUICKLY.

39:04.646 --> 39:07.170
LOOK, YOU ALL ABOUT CONTROL.

39:07.214 --> 39:09.695
NOW, I'M NOT GONNA DENY
THAT'S A TURN-ON.

39:09.738 --> 39:12.393
BUT YOU NEVER SHOW
YOUR CARDS.

39:12.437 --> 39:13.916
I FIGURED
IF I WENT ALL-IN

39:13.960 --> 39:15.222
I'D BE OUT
ON THE STREET SOMEWHERE

39:15.265 --> 39:16.658
WITH A TIN CUP
AND A BORROWED BLANKET.

39:16.702 --> 39:18.181
YOU WITH ME?

39:18.225 --> 39:20.401
FOR ABOUT 10 MORE SECONDS.

39:20.445 --> 39:23.491
BUT WHEN YOU BARGED INTO
THE RESTAURANT TO TELL ME OFF

39:23.535 --> 39:25.754
WELL, THAT WAS
A WHOLE NEW SIMONE

39:25.798 --> 39:27.060
BECAUSE THAT MEANT
YOU WERE...

39:27.103 --> 39:28.975
HIDING A SHRED
OF VULNERABILITY?

39:29.018 --> 39:32.718
WELL, HELL, A SHRED'S
BETTER THAN NOTHING.

39:32.761 --> 39:35.938
ALL I'M SAYING IS...

39:35.982 --> 39:39.638
...YOU SHOW ME YOUR CARDS,
I'LL SHOW YOU MINE.

39:44.469 --> 39:46.035
Narrator:
IT STRUCK EMERSON

39:46.079 --> 39:49.038
THAT WHILE SOME PEOPLE
ARE TERRIFIED OF A GAMBLE

39:49.082 --> 39:51.301
AND OTHERS CAN'T SAY NO TO ONE

39:51.345 --> 39:56.481
THE BEST APPROACH LIES
SOMEWHERE IN THE MIDDLE.

39:56.524 --> 39:58.613
I WOULD ASK WHAT CHANGED
YOUR MIND...

39:58.657 --> 40:00.093
EXCEPT?

40:00.136 --> 40:02.095
EXCEPT YOU HAVEN'T
RANG THE DOORBELL YET

40:02.138 --> 40:04.924
WHICH WOULD PROVE THAT
YOU HAVE CHANGED YOUR MIND.

40:04.967 --> 40:08.188
ALRIGHT, ANYTHING I SAY NOW
IS TEMPTING FATE.

40:08.231 --> 40:09.842
IT'S EASIER TO MAKE
ASSUMPTIONS ABOUT DAD

40:09.885 --> 40:13.585
AND WHY HE DID WHAT HE DID
THAN ADMIT I DON'T KNOW.

40:13.628 --> 40:15.282
I DON'T KNOW MY FAMILY

40:15.325 --> 40:19.112
OR WHAT IT WOULD BE LIKE
TO KNOW THEM.

40:19.155 --> 40:23.159
AND THE FINDING-OUT PART...
MAKES ME A LITTLE QUEASY.

40:23.203 --> 40:27.425
WELL, WHATEVER HAPPENS,
I'LL BE RIGHT HERE, OKAY?

40:27.468 --> 40:28.991
THANKS.

40:29.035 --> 40:30.515
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

40:30.558 --> 40:32.865
COME ON.
COME ON.

40:32.908 --> 40:34.475
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

40:35.171 --> 40:37.304
OHH.

40:37.347 --> 40:38.348
HELLO.

40:38.392 --> 40:40.481
HI. I'M NED.

40:40.525 --> 40:42.744
I THOUGHT I'D STOP BY BECAUSE...

40:42.788 --> 40:46.139
BASICALLY,
WE HAVE THE SAME DAD.

40:52.972 --> 40:54.364
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:59.500 --> 41:03.765
Narrator:
AS THE BROTHERS GAZED AT EACH
OTHER FOR THE FIRST TIME

41:03.809 --> 41:07.421
THE PIE MAKER SENSED
THIS GAMBLE WOULD PAY OFF

41:07.465 --> 41:10.642
IN WAYS HE COULD NEVER PREDICT.

41:12.600 --> 41:16.474
AND FROM HIS VANTAGE POINT
ACROSS THE STREET

41:16.517 --> 41:19.259
DWIGHT AGREED.
